<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>I am trying to use Zend_Gdata as per Google instructions. My whole file looks like:
&lt;?php
require_once 'Zend/Loader.php'; // the Zend dir must be in your include_path
Zend_Loader::loadClass('Zend_Gdata_YouTube');
Zend_Loader::loadClass('Zend_Gdata_ClientLogin');</p>

<p>When executing, I get:
PHP Warning:  require_once(Zend/Http/Response/Stream.php): failed to open stream: No such file or directory in /var/lib/gdata/library/Zend/Http/Client.php on line 50
PHP Fatal error:  require_once(): Failed opening required 'Zend/Http/Response/Stream.php' (include_path='.:/var/lib/gdata/library') in /var/lib/gdata/library/Zend/Http/Client.php on line 50</p>

<p>There aren't directory Called "Response" in "Http" folder.</p>

<p>Work arround: Comment line 50 in Client.php</p>

